<p><em>Forgive (Verb): </em></p>
<ul>
<li><i><em>Stop feeling angry or resentful towards (someone) for an offence, flaw, or mistake.</em></i></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><em>No longer feel angry about or wish to punish (an offence, flaw, or mistake).</em></li>
</ul>
<p>[Oxford online dictionary]</p>
<p>For six years Assad has waged a campaign of extermination against a people who rose for freedom. His crimes have been so well documented, by both testimony and photographic evidence, that the international community is left in little doubt that this man, and his regime, have perpetrated atrocities on such a scale that they amount to crimes against humanity. <a href="https://leilashami.wordpress.com/2017/08/04/the-act-of-forgiving-and-forgetting/#more-935" class="more-link">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&rarr;</span></a></p>
